    <note>Zhou(1) Chi [476] Bojun's [497] grandfather or granduncle. Liu(2) Yi's [1201] son-in-law, grandfather of the betrothed of Li(2) Gang's [8078] son, Li(2) K [4159]. His grandson-in-law, Zhang(1) Jin [3128], was the son of Li(2) Gang's [8078] sister. Both his daughter and his son were buried in Changzhou, Yixing county, which suggests a relationship with the Yixing zhang. According to Lou Yue's funerary inscription for a lineage member(?) Yuanqing [3251], the family were for centuries residents of Suichang. Zhejiang TZ, 124.2a; Li Gang, WJ, 169.2a, 170.2a-4a (wife, surname Liu, who died in 1121), 4b, 6a; SHY:ZG, 68.29b.</note>
